Here's a code snippet that could be used to create a dynamic web experience to divert attention from the main site to an alternative platform:

**Step 1: Create a landing page with a hook**

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Diversion Alert!</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Attention Required!</h1>
  <p>Due to unforeseen circumstances, we need to redirect you to a new platform.</p>
  <button id="redirect-btn">Proceed to Alternative Platform</button>
  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

**Step 2: Create a JavaScript script to handle the redirect**

```javascript
// script.js
document.getElementById("redirect-btn").addEventListener("click", function() {
  // Create a countdown timer to build anticipation
  let timer = 5;
  const intervalId = setInterval(function() {
    document.getElementById("timer").innerHTML = `Redirect in ${timer} seconds...`;
    timer--;
    if (timer === 0) {
      clearInterval(intervalId);
      window.location.href = "https://alternative-platform.com"; // Redirect to the alternative platform
    }
  }, 1000);
});
```

